SEE YOU IN 21 DAYS!!! 🦋🌞🏕️
Super excited to get off the grid for a few weeks and live in between the walls of the Grand Canyon 🛶 can’t wait to share the experiences that will be made. ✨

21 days of rafting in the Grand Canyon and I can’t even describe what I just experienced. 🏜️ And to look back after these last 21 days… I don’t know how to put what I feel into words. This trip was life changing to say the least. We left our mark in the canyon in the best way possible. I couldn’t have imagined this trip without every single person on it. 

I had no expectations, let alone the slightest idea of what I was getting myself into when I said yes to a 21 day rafting trip… with 15 other people (most I have never met). We’ve created something so great it brings tears to my eyes just thinking about how grateful I am to have had this opportunity. When you’re in the wilderness for 21 days, you really get to know the people around you. It’s crazy how alike we all really are. I’ve been filming a lot on this trip and am going to put together a video to share with everyone as much as I can. Thanks nature. 🌞✨🏕️🦋🧘‍♀️

I found this off Reddit a while ago and put it in my notes. It’s a great perspective and I think it’ll be helpful for whoever reads it. ✨

The mind is a bitch..and you have to accept it first. If you give away to your mind it will one day lead you to the mouth of a live volcano and you will still be wondering what you need to do. Just shutup your mind and control it. It happens all the time with so many people. Its nothing thats happening for the first time in human history. Mind strays back, desires impossible, brood over things that cannot be mend and weaves wave of desire around things that are not real.
Your best bet is to engage with life and get busy. Do something that takes your lot of time and attention. For example, join the gym and develop your physique or quit smoking if you do smoke, or do both things together. Challenge your limits and break them. Divert your thoughts and energy to something positive and constructive. It will make you stronger. Dont bother too much about your stray thoughts. Accept that mind keeps doing all these all the time. Accept instead of ignoring them or giving them undue importance. Keep moving. Thats all you need to do.

The best way to let go is to be true to yourself, no matter what. If it hurts to let them go, let it hurt. If it makes you mad they didn’t straighten up so you wouldn’t have to leave, be mad. If you want to hold on, hold on, but don’t make a fool of yourself/be desperate/wait forever. You have to forgive, for yourself, then decide on moving on. Just know that most things in life aren’t absolute. It takes time for decisions to be final, for feelings to disappate, and it’s gonna hurt. Best thing to do is just relinquish them from your life, until you forget they exist, if that’s what you want.

You can’t move forward if you keep rereading the last chapter!

There’s a beauty to being independent and doing your own thing that will naturally draw people to you.

Those feelings of grief may never go away, but what you do with those feelings is important. You can either allow them to consume you, or you can use them to uplift you.
Little snippets of home 💚

PRAY FOR MAUI 😭

Maui is on fire. People are in distress, scared, and dying. Fueled by strong winds, multiple fires continue to spread throughout the island of Maui. Brush fires in one area expand over 1000+ acres. It is beyond terrifying for everyone and no one can get a hold of their loved ones. Maui fire crews continue to battle multiple fires in these uncontained areas. An emergency proclamation has been issued. People are getting evacuated, the Coast Guard has been responding to impacted areas where residents are entering the ocean due to smoke and fire conditions. The country requested National Guard support. What can we do to help? There is a GoFundMe in which all donations will be made to Hawaii First Responders so we can take action to help Maui and her people.

The community has been helping in providing evacuation and refuge for those who have no home.

PSA: sent from a friend

Use your energy to believe, create, love, grow, glow, manifest, and heal. Accepting the unknown isn’t about discovering something new and better, but about becoming something new and better. It’s not going to click into place straight away. Focus on the next thought, the next action, one day at a time, until one day you will look back and see how far you’ve come. Things take time. Under the tragedy is a full life of healing waters. Future days of restoration. Thank you Maui. 🫶🏻 #mauistrong #ahupuaʻa #lahainastrong

Education is key. 🔑✍️
•
•
Beyond grateful to be guided and trained by some of the most amazing teachers in this life. I’m talking sharks and humans. There is so much to learn about these ancient creatures that have been roaming the seas for almost 450 million years! ((that’s older than trees 🌱)). We can coexist with these magnificent animals 🦈. Especially when the time is taken to educate oneself and continue to respect the environment in which you enter. Sharks communicate to one another with their body language. Because of this form of communication, we humans do our best to interpret after observing, acknowledging, and respecting what the sharks are telling us. When done right, it is an experience you will never forget. After all, we are all part of nature. 🧘‍♀️

Been making a cozy home here 🫶🏻

It’s already October and to think back on everything that has happened so far this year is surreal. I know this has been one of the biggest years of my life, finding my people, discovering my greatest passions, opening doors to experiences I could only have dreamt of. There’s been moments where I stood in awe of everything before me, realizing why everything had to happen the way it did. The dark days pushed me out of my comfort zone in so many ways mentally, emotionally, and physically. The process of feeling unfathomably uncomfortable, yet pushing beyond that is probably one of the most rewarding experiences anyone could have in life. If you push beyond the uncomfortability of things with confidence and a positive mindset, you will always win. Cheers to this next chapter and embracing the art of slowing down. Captured by my dear friend @davidpariasphoto resembling to flow and to embracing the slow. 🪸
